{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce Government Spending on Consultancies",
        "additional_details": "We think Government departments rely too heavily on costly external consultants, even for tasks civil servants could do. Reports show some contracts charge \u00a33,000+ per day per consultant, draining public funds while frontline services face cuts. By capping consultant fees and boosting in-house skills, we think we could save billions and reinvest in the NHS, education, and infrastructure.",
        "background": "Reduce government spending on private consultants, which has risen 57% in the past five years, costing taxpayers \u00a33.4 BN in 2024. Prioritise in-house expertise, enforce spending caps, and require full transparency on all consultancy contracts to ensure value for money.",
